A heap tree is a binary tree that satisfies:

âœ… Complete Binary Tree property

âœ… Heap Order Property (either min-heap or max-heap)

Min heap
        1
      /   \
     3     5
    / \   /
   7   9  6

Max heap

        9
      /   \
     7     6
    / \   /
   3   1  5

Heap
A  heap refers to:

A specialized tree-based data structure

Usually implemented as an array

Follows either min-heap or max-heap rules

âœ… Efficient for:

Inserting elements

Deleting min/max

Priority Queue operations

Tree view:
        1
      /   \
     3     5
    / \   /
   7   9  6

Array: [1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 6]

Left child: 2*i + 1

Right child: 2*i + 2

Parent: (i - 1) / 2

Applications of Heap

CPU Scheduling (Priority Queue)

Dijkstraâ€™s Algorithm (Min Heap)

Huffman Coding

Heap Sort

